    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="section" id="faq" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>What is TDS on lottery winnings?</h3>
                    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>TDS (Tax Deducted at Source) is a tax of 30% deducted on lottery winnings exceeding ₹10,000. This is deducted under Section 194B of the Income Tax Act before you receive your prize money.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>Do I need to file IT return for lottery winnings?</h3>
                    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Yes, lottery winnings must be declared in your income tax return under "Income from Other Sources" regardless of the amount. You can claim credit for TDS already deducted.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>Is there any additional tax apart from TDS?</h3>
                    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Yes, if your total income including lottery winnings falls in higher tax brackets, you may need to pay additional tax. However, you can claim credit for the 30% TDS already deducted.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>Can I reduce tax on lottery winnings?</h3>
                    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>The 30% TDS is mandatory and cannot be reduced. However, you can invest part of your winnings in tax-saving instruments to reduce overall tax liability on other income.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>What documents do I need for claiming lottery winnings?</h3>
                    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>You need the original winning ticket, valid ID proof, PAN card, and address proof. For winnings above ₹10,000, you'll also receive a TDS certificate (Form 16A).</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <h3>How accurate is this calculator?</h3>
                    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>This calculator provides accurate TDS calculations based on current Indian tax laws. However, consult a tax professional for complex situations or significant winnings.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

